-- Deutsche Boerse says Clearstream cooperating with U.S. authorities
-- By Maria Sheahan
-- Wed Apr 02, 2014 02:07AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, April 2 (Reuters) - Deutsche Boerse <DB1Gn.DE> said its Clearstream Banking SA business is cooperating with U.S. authorities investigating it in connection with alleged violations of U.S. money laundering and Iran sanction laws.

"The investigation is in a very early stage," Deutsche Boerse said in a statement on Wednesday.